        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 7 at 2:21AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 221 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Aguilares, or 21 miles southeast of Laredo, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oilton, Mirando City, Aguilares, and Bruni.

This includes US Highway 83 between mile markers 730 and 734.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
